The paper deals with a geometric packing problem involving rectangles and squares, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of sorted order along the boundary of the square suggests that there may be some data structure or algorithmic technique involved, which could place it in the data structures (cs.DS) or algorithms (cs.DM) sub-categories. The problem also involves maximizing the total area of the rectangles, which suggests a combinatorial optimization (cs.CO) or game theory (cs.GT) sub-category. However, since the problem is primarily geometric in nature, the first three sub-categories are more likely.
